    "summary": "Over 20 years of experience in continental Europe & Asia Pacific region with multifunctional experience in Finance, Commercial and Operations in multinational companies at global head office levels. Having worked, lived and traveled extensively around the world for work and leisure, I view my work through an international lens.\n\nIndustry experience: Sustainable energy, Innovation ecosystems & start-ups, Express distribution, Supply chain and Ed-tech.\n\n50 thousand feet thinker with storytelling & public speaking skills and two decades of 50 feet execution experience. \n\nHe has investor relations experience in capital raising with the capital markets i.e.: debt and equity markets. He is knowledgeable in translating to the external investors (large commercial banks and largest private equities) both: (1) the company\u2019s operating model (i.e.: how we operate and how we convert inputs into outputs), and (2) the financial business model, audited financial statements and different valuation methods of the company\u2019s 250+ minority holdings (IFRS valuation, last round valuation and VC valuation methods).\n\nVery high affinity to technology and comfortable with concepts of physics, chemistry, mathematics, and computing needed to understand technology & innovation. That enables sparring with technical experts on technology concepts to validate the business case & financial case for the end customer and fit for the company business model.\n\nThe geographic area of responsibility: Global scope.\n\nResponsible for: End to end operations and delivery.\n\nKey strengths: \n- Communicating and simplifying complex business concepts to stakeholders across the layers of the organization.\n- Ability to tailor & translate initiatives and market trends in the company's business model.\n- Wide IT experience & super-user capabilities, design & build of IT systems, and maintenance of IT environments.  \n\nExpertise: Performance/Project Management, Business Reviews, EU Funding & Grant Management, Triple bottom line fund management, Internal Consultancy, Cost Control, Activity Based Costing, Cross-functional team leadership, Global Multi-country projects, Business Analysis, Financial Modelling, Business Planning, Pricing, IT/Financial systems testing & implementation and Business Partnering.\n\nEnthusiast: Philosophy, Theoretical Physics & Mental Models.",
